# Documentation

## Previa Context

This is user-facing documentation for Previa, an AI-powered prediction market intelligence platform. Docs explain how traders use the web app to browse markets, view AI scores, set alerts, link trading accounts, and manage their account.

## Structure

- Navigation defined in `docs.json` — update when adding pages
- Reusable fragments in `snippets/` — import via MDX
- Each section maps to a web app feature area

## Writing Rules

- Task-oriented: title = what user wants to do, body = steps, end = expected result
- Every page stands alone — no "see above" or "as mentioned"
- Use Mintlify components: `<Card>`, `<CardGroup>`, `<Tabs>`, `<Callout>`, `<Steps>`
- Lead with the outcome, not the feature name
- Define prediction market terms on first use
- Keep quickstart under 5 minutes

## Page Template

```mdx
---
title: "Action-Oriented Title"
description: "One sentence describing what the user will learn"
---

Brief intro paragraph.

<Steps>
  <Step title="First step">
    Instructions with screenshots where helpful.
  </Step>
  <Step title="Second step">
    More instructions.
  </Step>
</Steps>

## Next steps

Link to related pages.
```
